sentences: Yasuo Namekawa (born 23 March 1987), better known by his stage name Kangnam, is a Korean-Japanese singer and television personality who was the vocalist and oldest member of the South Korean hip-hop group M.I.B. He made his first recording in South Korea with the single "Say My Name" just before becoming a member of M.I.B.

sentences: Career in South Korea (2011–present)
In South Korea, Kangnam first performed as a member of M.I. B under the Jungle Entertainment label on 25 October 2011, with the title track "G.D. M", which stands for "Girls, Dreams, Money".
His solo song, "Say My Name", was released on 17 October 2011, as part of a spin-off promotion to prove that each member was capable of standing alone.
In 2012, Kangnam appeared in a TV advertisement for Epson, an electronics company that specializes in image-related products, and took on his first acting role in the TV sitcom 21st
In October 2014, he became a permanent cast member of MBC's I Live Alone.
In November 2014, he became an exclusive model for the shoe store ABC Mart, with model Nam Joo-hyuk.
Kangnam finally saw the fruit of his labours towards the end of 2014, when he was the presenter for a year-end festival stage as part of the "Lucky Boys" project for 2014 SBS Gayo Daejun.
"On 26 December 2014, Kangnam released his second solo track, "What Do I Do", which wentsoared to #1 on Daum's real-time charts.
In February 2015, he was appointed the honorary ambassador for the fourth KCON music festival and convention for its first time in Japan and performed at the concert on 22 April.
Solo career in Japan (2016)
Kangnam released his first Japanese solo album, Ready to Fly, on 25 May 2016, under CJ Victor Entertainment.
On 16 March 2019, Kangnam's agency confirmed that he and the Olympic speed skater Lee Sang-hwa were dating.
On 11 August 2019, Kangnam announced his decision to forfeit his Japanese citizenship and began the process of becoming a naturalized Korean citizen.
Kangnam married Lee on 12 October 2019.
In the 3 October 2014, episode of I Live Alone Rainbow segment, Kangnam revealed that he had only $3 in his bank account.
As an only child, he spent most of his childhood in Japan and also spent some years in Hawaii.
